item.description:
A linear programming formulation can be put into either the general form or standard form. General Form $$  egin{align} 	ext{min.} \quad &amp; \mathbf{c}^T \mathbf{x} 
ewline 	ext{s.t.} \quad &amp; \mathbf{A} x \geq b 
ewline \end{align} $$ Standard Form $$  egin{align} 	ext{min.} \quad &amp; \mathbf{c}^T \mathbf{x} 
ewline 	ext{s.t.} \quad &amp; \mathbf{A} x = b 
ewline &amp; \mathbf{x} \geq 0 \end{align} $$
